[
    {
        "content": "<p>I've noticed that this code compiles, but it panics at runtime:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>:<span class=\"kt\">f32</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">4.2</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{}\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"fm\">format_args!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"{x:?}\"</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Should it be a compile time error instead? (similar to regular formatting <code>{x}</code>)</p>",
        "id": 372550167,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1688555367
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a panic message?</p>",
        "id": 372553675,
        "sender_full_name": "Esteban Blanc",
        "timestamp": 1688556123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto-rust/pull/422#discussion_r1252168592\">https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto-rust/pull/422#discussion_r1252168592</a></p>",
        "id": 372554984,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1688556391
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rust output the same thing for <code>Display</code> and <code>Debug</code>:<br>\n<a href=\"https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2021&amp;gist=9ae6e55b40d50d27253d79d3238a8a14\">https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2021&amp;gist=9ae6e55b40d50d27253d79d3238a8a14</a></p>\n<p>So I guess in our case, if we don't support regular formating, we shouldn't support the debug format either.</p>\n<p>IMAO yes, it makes sens to have a compile error here</p>",
        "id": 372559572,
        "sender_full_name": "Esteban Blanc",
        "timestamp": 1688557329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's a panic because we can't make it a compile time error.</p>",
        "id": 372561746,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1688557770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>libcore needs Debug for f32 to be implemented, so I can't just remove the impl of Debug. But at the same time we don't want libcore to generate any fp code either, so I made it a panic.</p>",
        "id": 372562102,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1688557843
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In retrospect a should probably just make it output \"f32\" instead</p>",
        "id": 372562159,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1688557859
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thanks for the explanation</p>",
        "id": 372619841,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1688568636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I'm trying to build my first Rust kernel module.<br>\nI looked at the <code>rust-out-of-tree</code> module for reference, and I came up with this:<br>\n<code>hello_world.rs</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">prelude</span>::<span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span>: <span class=\"nc\">MyRustyKmod</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"hello_world\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">author</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"rdbo\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">description</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"Hello World kernel module in Rust\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">license</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">MyRustyKmod</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyRustyKmod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Hello World from my rusty kernel module</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Drop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyRustyKmod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Goodbye World from my rusty kernel module</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>Makefile</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Makefile\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">obj-m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>hello_world.o\n\n<span class=\"nv\">KDIR</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>/lib/modules/<span class=\"k\">$(</span>shell<span class=\"w\"> </span>uname<span class=\"w\"> </span>-r<span class=\"k\">)</span>/build\n<span class=\"nv\">PWD</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>shell<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">pwd</span><span class=\"k\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nf\">default</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>MAKE<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-C<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>KDIR<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>PWD<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>modules\n\n<span class=\"nf\">clean</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>MAKE<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-C<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>KDIR<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>PWD<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>clean\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>When I run <code>make</code>, I get the following error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">modules</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"mf\">6.1.38</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">build</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">someone</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Repos</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">modules</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Entering</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">directory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">headers</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mf\">6.1.38</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lts</span><span class=\"o\">'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">someone</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Repos</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">hello_world</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"./rust/target.json\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">does</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exist</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">build</span>:<span class=\"mi\">307</span>: <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">someone</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Repos</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">hello_world</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">2012</span>: <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">someone</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Repos</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Leaving</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">directory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'/</span><span class=\"n\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">headers</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mf\">6.1.38</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lts</span><span class=\"o\">'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">7</span>: <span class=\"nc\">default</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What is <code>./rust/target.json</code> supposed to be? I don't see it anywhere</p>",
        "id": 373879664,
        "sender_full_name": "Rdbo",
        "timestamp": 1688979864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the kernel has Rust support:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grep</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"na\">RUST</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">boot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lts</span>\n<span class=\"n\">CONFIG_HAVE_RUST</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 373880243,
        "sender_full_name": "Rdbo",
        "timestamp": 1688979994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You also need <code>CONFIG_RUST</code> to be set.</p>",
        "id": 373880913,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1688980131
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What is the difference between <code>CONFIG_HAVE_RUST</code> and <code>CONFIG_RUST</code>? I thought <code>CONFIG_HAVE_RUST</code> meant the kernel had Rust support, no?</p>",
        "id": 373889187,
        "sender_full_name": "Rdbo",
        "timestamp": 1688981753
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <code>HAVE_RUST</code> just says that you _can_ use Rust, but you're not actually doing so unless <code>RUST</code> is also specified.</p>",
        "id": 373889673,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1688981837
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, ok. It seems I'll have to build my own Linux kernel with Rust support. Thank you</p>",
        "id": 373890076,
        "sender_full_name": "Rdbo",
        "timestamp": 1688981919
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"631403\">@Rdbo</span> For ArchLinux I created a kernel package with Rust support enabled: <a href=\"https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/linux-rust\">https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/linux-rust</a> this may help you for you own kernel. I documented the process to create it on my blog: <a href=\"https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module.html\">https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module.html</a></p>",
        "id": 375998588,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1689595835
    }
